./CHANGELOG.md:607:- Added depth-2 syncopation-features end-to-end test coverage (frac-0117): `tests/test_syncopation_features.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `SyncopationFeaturesEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing syncopation + polyrhythmic-cross surface across `my-claw/tools/senseweave/groove_engine.py` and `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py` through one realistic groove lifecycle: `_GROOVE_PROFILES["syncopated"]` and `_GROOVE_PROFILES["polyrhythmic_cross"]` resolve to registered profiles with non-zero `syncopation_intensity` and non-empty `lane_phase_offsets` (with `polyrhythm == (3, 4)` for the cross profile), `_parse_lane_phase_offsets("0,1,2,3,1")` agrees with the directly supplied `(0, 1, 2, 3, 1)` tuple, `syncopate_phrase(...)` at `intensity=1.0` deterministically inserts leading rests into a four-note melody phrase while preserving total duration and stamping `metadata["syncopated"] == "true"`, the same call at `intensity=0.6` produces at least as many melody rests as bass rests under the same RNG seed, `_quantize_phrase_to_lane(... phase_offset_rows=2)` shifts the melody first step row to row 2 while exempting the bass first step row at row 0, and a primitive diagnostic of profiles, parsed offsets, rest counts, durations, first-step rows, and `DEFAULT_LANE_PHASE_OFFSETS` round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_syncopation_features_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2, requires the named end-to-end class/method, and requires the machine-readable `depth: 2` marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the syncopation + polyrhythmic-cross surface already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4673 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
