./CHANGELOG.md:699:- Added depth-2 generation composer-hook end-to-end test coverage (frac-0077): `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` now includes `GenerationComposerHookEndToEndTests`, which drives the public composer-hook surface (`_should_queue_now`, `build_generation_request`, `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, `MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD`) plus the duet-composer integration `_post_song_generation_hook` through the full gate -> build -> enqueue cycle. The end-to-end scenarios cover a happy-path enqueue with a real builder via a thin `_ConditionerAdapter` that asserts the queued payload equals `build_generation_request(...)`, idempotency key matches `request_hash`, and the request hash is a 64-char content-addressed digest; gate-denial paths for low daily budget at the `MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD` floor, sampler-dominating antipatterns, working-ambience low arc payoff, and rate-limited recent enqueue under `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, all confirming `_post_song_generation_hook` returns `None` with no queue traffic; deterministic-builder identity for equal inputs and distinct hashes/seeds for changed mode or arc phase; and a JSON-safe round-trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)` on the built request and the queued payload. `tests/test_test_generation_composer_hook_depth.py` pins `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function composer-hook assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/composer_hook.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4514 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:701:- Added depth-2 generation client protocol end-to-end test coverage (frac-0076): `tests/test_generation_client_protocol.py` now includes `GenerationClientProtocolEndToEndTests`, which drives a typed `GenerationRequest` through a structural `GenerationClient`, typed `GenerationResult` output, JSON-safe `result_summary`, `cost_per_second`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` success/failure diagnostics. `tests/test_test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins the protocol test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` behavior remains unchanged because the protocol helpers already produced meaningful output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4508 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:703:- Added depth-2 generation cache end-to-end test coverage (frac-0075): `tests/test_generation_cache.py` now includes `GenerationCacheEndToEndTests`, which drives the public `GenerationCache` API through the full miss → put → hit → replace cycle (asserting content-addressed filenames, suffix preservation, accessed-at LRU updates, and in-place byte replacement), the queue/storage `set`/`get` aliases sharing a single on-disk entry with `put`/`lookup`, a JSON-safe index round-trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`, a multi-entry restart that recovers surviving entries while pruning a payload deleted out-of-band, and a combined count + size LRU cap where an explicit lookup keeps the oldest entry warm and forces eviction of the middle entry. `tests/test_test_generation_cache_depth.py` pins `tests/test_generation_cache.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function generation cache assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/cache.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4504 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:705:- Added depth-2 garden watcher end-to-end test coverage (frac-0074): `tests/test_garden_watcher.py` now includes `GardenWatcherEndToEndTests`, which drives the public garden watcher path through deterministic brightness/time snapshot building, JSON-safe operator summary generation, and atomic runtime-state persistence. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/garden_watcher.py` now exposes `build_garden_state`, `summarize_garden_state`, and `write_current_garden_state`, while `update_garden_state` delegates through the deterministic builder so existing callers keep the same one-path behavior. `tests/test_test_garden_watcher_depth.py` pins the garden watcher test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4498 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
